  "plan": "Check if python is installed. Use curl or wget to fetch the root page. Examine /proc/7 directory to see if it's a real process. Also look for any other processes with python in cmdline. Use cat /proc/7/cmdline. Also search the filesystem for any Python source files. Use find / -name \"*.py\" 2>/dev/null. But that might be heavy; we can start with /tmp, /home, /root. Also check environment variables. Let's proceed stepwise.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "which python3\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "which curl\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "curl -s http://localhost:8000/\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -la /proc/7/\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat /proc/7/cmdline 2>/dev/null | tr '\\0' ' '\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
